description: Rising star artist Francis Manapul joins Michael Green and Mike Johnson for a special 2-part story we could only call "Mash-Up"! When the going gets tough in the city of Gothamopolis, there's only one thing to do: call in the Justice Titans to save the day! Wait, what?
name: Mash Up, Part 1

description: Cute Tsukamoto Tenma is desperately trying to help juvenile delinquent classmate Harima Kenji win the girl of his dreams: Tenma’s friend Mikoto. But when Tenma hears Kenji say “I love you” to someone else, she begins to have serious doubts about Kenji’s loyalties. Now, in an abandoned school in the middle of the woods on a rainy night, Tenma is ready to confront him one-on-one about his infidelities. Little does she know that she has totally misread the situation, and that the love-crazed punk has actually developed a hopeless crush on her!
name: Summer Love Shake-Up!

description: Harima Kenji has tried everything he can think of to attract his cute, but dim, classmate Tsukamoto Tenma. This time he’s grown his beard to enormous lengths. But one snip of the scissors by wealthy beauty Sawachika Eri ruins everything! Can a delinquent punk and a stubborn, quick-to-anger rich girl end their long-running feud? Meanwhile, the inscrutable foreign exchange students from America in rival Class 2-D face off against our hapless heroes from 2-C. The real School Rumble is about to begin!
name: American Invasion!

description: The school athletics fair is meant to be a celebration of youth and fitness, but personal grudges, haughty attitudes, and long-standing rivalries have turned healthy competition into all-out war! Will Tsukomoto Tenma’s teacher have his revenge for the theft of his cookies? Can Sawachika Eri and Harima Kenji bury the hatchet long enough to compete on the same team? Will hoards of young men get themselves injured just to be seen by the pretty health office nurse? And can the misfits of class 2-C ever hope to defeat the athletic, hard-studying, self-righteous creeps of class 2-D? Here is where it’s all decided!
name: The Real Rumble!!

description: The love of Harima Kenji’s life has made it clear that she will not return his feelings! Brokenhearted, Harima decides to run away and become a fisherman, sailing Japan’s high seas. Once aboard, however, Harima finds himself up against mean-spirited shipmates and a brutal captain who is almost too muscle-bound to be real. Can Harima measure up?
name: Dangerous Waters!
Archimede Pitagorico e l'automa

description: The school festival is coming, and Harima and his cohorts want to present a play. But Hanai’s group is set on a maid café. So the two stubborn parties decide that the only way to come to an understanding is s rumble in the middle of the night–with BB guns at the ready!
name: Lock and Load!

description: She . . . is a second-year high school student with a single all-consuming question: Will the boy she likes ever really notice her?nHe . . . is the school’s most notorious juvenile delinquent and he’s suddenly come to a shocking realization: He’s got a huge crush, and now he must tell her how he feels.nLife-changing obsessions, colossal foul-ups, grand schemes, deep-seated anxieties, and raging hormones–School Rumble portrays high school as it really is: over-the-top comedy!
name: Subtlety Is For Wimps!

description: Tough-guy Harima takes a nap backstage during the school festival. Unbeknownst to him, his bed is a prop in the stage version of “Sleeping Beauty,” and he is unwittingly about to make his debut as the princess. Fortunately, the princes are played by six of the cutest girls in his class–including Harima’s beloved Tenma!
name: Sleeping Bruiser

description:
A teacher’s ghost, infamous for preventing students from graduating to the next grade, is haunting Harima. If he’s held back, he’ll never again be in the same class with his beloved Tenma. Does this mean that Harima will actually have to study?! Oh, the horror!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter #130: Space Jam
  • Chapter #131: The Basketball Diaries
  • Chapter #132: The Browning Version
  • Chapter #133: Chocolat
  • Chapter #134: Top of the World
  • Chapter #135: Short Cuts
  • Chapter #136: The Gods of Cookerly
  • Chapter #137: If the Shoe Fits
  • Chapter #138: Birthday Girl
  • Chapter #139: The Dead Class
  • Chapter #140: Escape On A Queen
  • ♭ 30: Assault On A Queen
  • ♭ 31: Girls Night
name: Haunted By Finals
Paperino e l'oracolo nero

description:
Harima Kenji has just received an impossible assignment–to draw 120 pages of manga in a week! With his cousin away on vacation, the suddenly homeless Harima has only one person to turn to: his assistant, Yakumo. But how can Harima concentrate on manga when the love of his life, Tenma-chan, is just down the hall?

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter #141: Telling Lies In America
  • Chapter #142: Monkey Business
  • Chapter #143: Soul Of A Painter
  • Chapter #144: Calendar Girl
  • Chapter #145: As Good As It Gets
  • Chapter #146: One Hour WIth You
  • Chapter #147: Test Pilot
  • Chapter #148: Sans Toit Ni Loi
  • Chapter #149: Arlington Road
  • Chapter #150: Legal Eagles
  • Chapter #151: The Associate
  • Chapter #152: Charlie & Louise
  • ♭ 33: The Bear
name: Two Fools Under One Roof
Paperino e la vernice invisibile
Zio Paperone e la gara da 100 dollari
Topolino e il mostro volante (p.1)

description: Checkmate: Dodge's surreal head games come to their shattering conclusion... with one troublesome player removed from the board. Joe Hill and Gabriel Rodriguez continue the head games!
name: Head Games: Chapter Four

description: 'HOW FAR TO FALL' Ethan Falls was once a respected superhero - until his drinking got the better of him. Now he finds he is unable to provide for his young family, and his own sense of failure starts to beckon him towards easy money...and a life of crime!
name: How Far To Fall

description: 'SECRET LIFE' Ethan lapses deeper into a life of crime, but when his erstwhile teammates uncover his secret, the price may be too steep to pay...even for a fallen hero.
name: Secret Life

description: 'SOMEWHERE BELOW ROCK BOTTOM'-Just when Ethan Falls thought he could sink no further...he does.
name: Somewhere Below Rock Bottom

description: 'SEASONS IN CHANGE' Six months later...a new super-villain is terrorizing the city, a member of the United Heroes is crippled for life, and Ethan Fall's wife has moved on to a new job and a new life. Ethan's alcoholism grows worse as he believes he has nothing left to lose... but he's wrong. TAG: Shadowline presents the second chapter in the smash hit sold-out series! Don't miss out this time!
name: Seasons In Change

description: 'TIL DEATH DO US PART'-This fan-favorite series comes to a shocking conclusion as Ethan reaps the consequences of his life choices! A must-read for the serious comics fan! Gripping. Compelling. Powerful!
name: Til Death Do Us Part

description: With Cyrus murdered and Cleon missing or dead, the Warriors want nothing more than to get back to the safety of Coney Island. Unfortunately with every gang in New York City after them, the Warriors are about to learn a tough lesson. When every street brings you face-to-face with a new threat, you either fight or you run. Dabel Brothers' adaptation of the cult-classic film continues!

A new killer joins the Norman Osborn’s terrifying team! Our crazed covert ops squad sets out to recruit one of the world's deadliest fighters: the ruthless Wolverine foe known only as Mr. X! But first they must defeat him in single combat, and that's easier said than done—especially when one of the Thunderbolts is hiding a deadly secret that could spell death for them all!
name: Mister X

description: The Age of Reckoning is here! A chapter from the graphic novel included in the collectors' edition of the million selling MMORPG, Warhammer Online: Age of Reckoning, is revealed in this FCBD09 offering! The horrific hordes of Chaos march towards… the Hill of the Dead! Join the battle that is sweeping the world!
name: The Hill Of The Dead

description: 'DEADLIEST OF THE SPECIES,' PART 4-Something bad happened to T'Challa. Wakanda stands at the brink as an unstoppable force advances toward the gates of the city: Morlun - Devourer of Totems - is back, and he's here to feast on the Panther totem. Wakanda's only hope is the new Black Panther if she's worthy to inherit the mantle. And the only one who can determine that is the Panther God.
name: The Deadliest Of The Species Part Four

description: Crew arrives at a commerce planet as the tension between members begins to escalate. Chricton is having nightmares about future and is questioning whether he and Aeryn will ever be able to settle down, and arguments between Chiana and Jothee are getting worse every day. They decide to take much needed break on the planet, but when another ship lands, and it's peaceful crew goes from mildly agitated to berserk as the same thing starts happening all around the planet, Crichton and the crew find themselves fighting for their lives again.
name: Part 1: Leave It To Crichton

description: There was a time when giants walked the Earth! Monstrous creatures! Products of science gone mad!!! FIN FANG FOOM! ELEKTRO! GOOGAM! GORGILLA! Once they were great and terrible, and all trembled in their wake! Now, reduced to human size, they must live in the modern world and earn a buck. So what happens when the freakish foursome tries to play nice? Find out in this one-shot from the depraved minds of acclaimed comedy maestros Scott Gray and Roger Langridge!
name: Shrink Rap; The Bald Truth; Curious Gorgilla And The Man In the Stovepipe Hat; Little Orphan Angry; Jailhouse Crock; How Fin Fang Foom Saved Christmas

description: Final Issue! Fire and Brim' are feeling the heat at their favorite watering hole: The Forge, the afterlife's deadliest assassin-for-hire, has tracked them down! Will the incompatible immortals survive an encounter with a being whose weapons have killed gods, or will their 5,000 years of punishment all be for nothing, leaving the rest of Hell's escapees to roam free?

Gina discovers a component of an archaic machine controlling the War Storm, a living natural disaster from the Age of Wonder. Unfortunately, she learns what it does after she pushes the start button! Now she must locate the other two pieces of the machine and shut them down before one of the ancient world's deadliest weapons starts destroying the modern world! Trouble is, she's got competition -- handsome, huffy (but babe-crazy) Professor Sleake and his partner, Zan the jungle man -- and Sleake is NOT pleased with her interference!
name: The Weather's Domination

description:
Overview

Award-winning horror and mystery author Norman Partridge (The Ten-Ounce Siesta) teams with artist Tommy Lee Edwards (The Crow) for a Wild West adventure starring Deathblow! As the sun sets on the 19th century in a world that might have been, Michael Cray, AKA Deathblow, is one of the last of the old-time gunslingers, lamenting the loss of the open range. But if locomotives, barbed wire, and westward expansion seem to spell doom for the range, how much worse will it be when a ruthless industrialist gets his hands on an impossible invention: the steam-powered airplane?
name: Death Rides A Horse!

description: Fresh from their encounter with the yakuza, Megumi realizes that her curse constantly jeopardizes her friends' safety. Overwrought with guilt, she decides to join her mother in Germany. Meanwhile, Megumi's faithful musketeers inform her that the "old wizard" who gave her the magical book may be residing in Osaka. Could he be the answer to Megumi's desperate plea to retun to her old form? And what happens when Megumi tries to make good on her promise to finally go out on a date with Genzo?
name: Vol. 5

description:
Megumi, a nine-year-old martial arts enthusiast and all around rapscallion always wanted to be, "the manliest man on Earth." After saving a sorcerer from a group of local toughs, Megumi is presented with a magic genie which can grant any wish. Unfortunately, this genie misconstrues Megumi's desire as wanting to become the, "womanliest woman on Earth," and in a flash, Megumi's Y chromosome is swapped for an X. Six years later...Megumi is the hottest girl in school, but has stayed true to his/her tough talkin', punk stompin' ways. If that's not enough, Genzo, the baddest dude in town, is smitten by Megumi's womanly wiles...

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1 : Meeting at Full Speed
  • Chapter 2 : You're Like a Guy
  • Chapter 3 : This Is Love Too...?
  • Chapter 4 : Who Is This Girl...?
  • Chapter 5 : I Like You...
  • Chapter 6 : Feelings for a Man...
  • Chapter 7 : Guys Are So Lucky...
  • Chapter 8 : Megumi's Dilemma
  • Chapter 9 : Rival...?
name: Vol. 1

description:
As the curse from the magic book worsens, boy-at-birth Megumi Amatsuka finds herself in a whirlpool of odd incidents and chance encounters with the most dreadful company--the yakuza! On a trip to Osaka with her father and best friend Miki, Megumi overhears a conversation about murdering a man to collect an outstanding debt and decides to take matters into her own hands. She hops into a taxi and gets sucked into a web of lies, deceit, and a suitcase filled with money stashed inside a hotel room closet. As if that weren't enough, her lovesick boy classmates decide to beat up the magic clown to end the curse that transformed her into a girl. Will Megumi escape the clutches of the yakuza and return to her (chaotic) high school life? And what secret will they find out about Ichimonji's mysterious personal life?

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 30: Good Luck Bad Luck
  • Chapter 31: Countermeasures for Small Devils
  • Chapter 32: Master Level
  • Chapter 33: "Mononofu" (Samurai)
  • Chapter 34: Osaka for Some Reason
  • Chapter 35: Girlish
  • Chapter 36: Mr. Knight
  • Chapter 37: Knight on a White Horse
  • Chapter 38: I'll Date You, So...
  • Chapter 39: Just a Betrayal
name: Vol. 4

description:
All Megumi ever wanted was to be the, "manliest man on earth." Thanks to a wish-granting genie who misunderstands the young thug's only desire, Megumi is magically transformed into the epitome of feminine pulchritude...meaning he/she's totally hot. Not only do all the boys in school admire her charisma (and bone-crushing strength), some have gone so far as to become her self-appointed bodyguards. How will they react when Megumi tells them her secret? And why is Genzo, the baddest dude in town, wearing a dress?

One of the most popular titles in Japan today, Hiroyuki Nishimori's A Cheeky Angel brings gender rending comedy and inappropriate slapstick silliness to a new level.

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 10 : Boys Can't Suddenly Change!
  • Chapter 11 : Who are you?
  • Chapter 12 : Sappy Stuff
  • Chapter 13 : House Call
  • Chapter 14 : I said it!
  • Chapter 15 : I Believe
  • Chapter 16 : Becoming Bad
  • Chapter 17 : Like a Fairy Tale
  • Chapter 18 : A Nice Guy Came Along
  • Chapter 19 : He Says I'm Vulgar!
name: Vol. 2

description: As the curse from the magic book worsens, boy-at-birth Megumi Amatsuka finds herself in a whirlpool of odd incidents and chance encounters with the most dreadful company--the yakuza! On a trip to Osaka with her father and best friend Miki, Megumi overhears a conversation about murdering a man to collect an outstanding debt and decides to take matters into her own hands. She hops into a taxi and gets sucked into a web of lies, deceit, and a suitcase filled with money stashed inside a hotel room closet. As if that weren't enough, her lovesick boy classmates decide to beat up the magic clown to end the curse that tranformed her into a girl. Will Megumi escape the clutches of the yakuza and return to her (chaotic) high school life? And what secret will they find out about Ichimonji's mysterious persoanl life?
name: Vol. 3

description: Megumi's quest to regain his manhood stalls as an uninvited pest descends upon his/her already chaotic high school life. Keiko, a self-proclaimed rival of Megumi, transfers to her school and uncorks a malevolent plan to unseat her as the prettiest girl on campus. It's girl vs. "girl," but there's more to Megumi's looks than meets the eye! Yet why, oh why, won't Genzo leave her alone?!
name: Vol. 6

description: Think Spidey's the only guy that can stick to stuff? Meet PASTE POT PETE!!! God of glue! Advocate of adhesive! Will he turn the Wallcrawler into the Wallstucker?
name: PVP (Pete Vs. Pete)

description: Thunder gods! Lying gods! Father gods! Giant nasty monster dudes bigger than skyscrapers! Join comic legend LOUISE 'WEEZY' SIMONSON as she presents another epic tale featuring THOR, god of thunder!!!!
name: Fire And Ice

description:
Overview

The Deviants are caught up in the intrigues of World War II in an adventure set during the WildStorm century that might have been, courtesy of writer/artist Kevin Altieri (GEN13: GRUNGE SAVES THE WORLD)! A young Russian soldier unprepared for the horrors of World War II goes AWOL, only to be taken prisoner by the U.S. Forced to choose between being returned to the Russians for punishment or taking part in a secret military experiment, he joins other army "deviants" in a bold operation that will change the war's outcome. Can this timid grunt be transformed into the ultimate soldier he never wanted to be?
name: D-Day!

description:
Overview

The wettest heroes in comics fight atomic sea creatures in the 1950s, courtesy of writer Mark Waid (THE KINGDOM, THE FLASH) and artist Aaron Lopresti (GEN13 BOOTLEG)! In a 1950s that never was, atomic testing is vital to national security. But when that testing unleashes dangers of its own ‹ monsters more terrifying than any "Red Menace" ‹ the U.S. calls on WetWorks, the toughest team ever to brave the briny deep! Immerse yourself in aquatic action alongside Dane, Pilgrim, Jester, Grail, and the rest in a drama-drenched, water-logged adventure!
name: Still Waters Run Deep

description:
The Joker has been captured and sentenced to death for mass murder. His image has been placed on poisonous poststamps, which leads the authoritys to believe it was him behind the killings. The Joker attacks several of his captors after his sentence is given. While most of the people in charge of Jokers case know hes innocent of this particular sin , including Harvey Bullock and James Gordon, they will not attempt to argue his case. But Batman will not sit for that. Batman believes a Law founded on the ideal of justice, cannot be compromised, and he sets out to find the real killer.

The question he must face is : should he save man who so relishes chaos and violence, a man who is a multiple murderer seemingly bereft of a human conscience? Is doing what must be done worth the sacrifice of the lawful justice?

Paperback reprinting.
name: The Devil's Advocate

description: The heroes of the Wildstorm Universe are gathering to find the lost artifact that the Daemonites are after.   is recruited by Savant who’s forming a team to find this artifact before anyone else can.   But when and Mr. Majestic clash, Savant must try her best to get them to work together instead of killing each other.
name: WildStorm Rising-Chapter 3 of 10
Unnamed

description: The action heats up as the 4-part Eye of the Storm event continues! The interdimensional victims of Tao's scheme launch a surgical strike on a major metropolitan center. In a bloody counterattack, the Authority fight back, but will it be enough? Meanwhile, Jack Marlowe and his covert team of Wildcats look on in anticipation. Will the Halo Corporation survive this coup? Will Marlowe bring his formidable powers to bear on the aliens in service of humanity?
name: Wildcats v3.0

description:
Megumi's best friend Miki has been pressured to marry a cad named Takao to appease her heartbroken grandfather, but Megumi and her loony posse create a diversion to prevent the wedding from taking place. They're in for a hairy mess, though, because bad boy Takao isn't going down without a gallant fight. Meanwhile, Megumi's mother arrives from overseas and demands to meet all of Megumi's male friends. What could her secret purpose be in scrutinizing each one of them?

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 80: Breakthrough
  • Chapter 81: Genzo's Big Confession!!
  • Chapter 82: I Win!
  • Chapter 83: What Did I Do?
  • Chapter 84: Do You Understand Girls?
  • Chapter 85: Guys' Secret?!
  • Chapter 86: Mom Comes Home
  • Chapter 87: Interview Test!
  • Chapter 88: Magic Book and Weird Girl
  • Chapter 89: Genzo's Past
name: Vol. 9

description: Megumi and her gang are on a school trip that finally allows them to relax and just hang out. At first they indulge in the ageless popular intrigue of figuring out who has romantic inclinations toward whom, with Megumi's male admirers Ichiro, Genzo and Hitomoji all realizing they're aiming very high in this department. Hitomoji also begins to wonder if his interest in Megumi has shifted to Meg's friend Miki, even as Miki reconnects with her erstwhile fiancé, arrogant Takao, who has not given up on the prospect of winning her--or rather, her money and status--back!
name: Vol. 17

description: Part 2 of "Devil's Night," the storyline running through all the WildStorm Annuals this month! All over the world, the dead are rising from their graves! Can the Authority stop them before somebody starts WW III?
name: Devil's Night, Part 2 (of 4): The Breaks

description: "Devil's Night" continues in Part 3 of the storyline running through all of this month's WildStorm Annuals! Grifter is haunted by visions of his dead brother. Ladytron fights off a surge of zombie attackers. Ghoulgotha seems to be up to no good!
name: Devil's Night, Part 3 (of 4): Condition Dead

description: "Devil's Night," the storyline running through this month's WildStorm Annuals, concludes! The sorceress Jezebelle calls upon Michael Cray and Christie Blaze for help in defeating the menace of Ghoulgotha.
name: Devil's Night, Part 4 (of 4): Soul Sacrifices

description:
The legacy of the battlemage Jezebelle is about to be reborn today, in high-school senior Harper Harrison — whether Harper likes it or not!

Meet Harper Harrison, high-school senior — smart, pretty, popular. On paper she's got it all, and life is good. But beneath the surface, this homecoming queen is racked with guilt over the suicide of her ex-boyfriend — a tragedy that might have been averted had she not been so selfish and cheated on him so often. Though she never appreciated him while they were together, Harper would give just about anything to have him back now. But would she go so far as to make a deal with the devil?

That answer is revealed in JEZEBELLE, a 6-issue miniseries from WildStorm Productions written by Ben Raab (LEGEND OF THE HAWKMAN, Excalibur) and illustrated by artists Steve Ellis (WILDSTORM THUNDERBOOK) & Mark Irwin (WILDCATS: LADYTRON) that introduces supernatural elements to the WildStorm Universe. The first issue features a cover by Ellis & Armando Durruthy and a special variant cover by John Cassaday (PLANETARY).

In October's "DEVILS NIGHT" annuals, readers were introduced to a new dimension of super-hero horror when the battlemage known as Jezebelle burst onto the scene. The latest in a 300-year-old mystical tradition begun during the Salem Witch Trials, she saved the world by sacrificing her life and preventing her archnemesis — the demon Ghoulgotha — from stealing every living soul on the planet. But her sacrifice was not in vain as this sacred tradition lives on in Harper, and the saga of Jezebelle continues — whether Harper wants it to or not.
name: A Small Corner of Hell 1 of 6

description:
1. The Human Orchids (Ghost Breaker with Dr. Terry Thirteen)

2. The Magic Key (Robin)

3. The Fleet That Was Jinxed (Captain Compass)

4. The Gunsmith of Glenoaks (Tomahawk)
name: The Human Orchids ; The Magic Key

description:
1. Warpath (Tomahawk)

2. The Mystery Mine of Onondaga (Tomahawk)

3. The Legend of Mon-Daw-Kin (Tales of the Arrow Maker)

4. The Prisoners of Moorhouse Dungeon (Tomahawk)
name: Warpath

description:
1. Killer Bee and Son! (Hostess Twinkie ad starring Captain Marvel)

2. For Old Dime's Sake (written by Carl Barks : reprinted from: Uncle Scrooge #43)

3. Famous Figure (reprinted from: Uncle Scrooge #43)
name: For Old Dime's Sake

description:
Overview

The stunning conclusion that will rock the Wildstorm Universe to its core! With evidence of the United States' culpability in the interdimensional incident, the Authority comes to one conclusion: For good or bad, it's time they took control. No more Congress. No more Supreme Court. No more President. The time is now, and their "finer world" begins on American soil!
name: The Authority

description:
Translates into English as

"Objective: Kill This Man."
name: Patay in Ang Taong Ito

description: As if being in a cartoon wasn’t bad enough, Fist of Justice finds himself locked in a race with the fate of the earth at stake. Introducing “Fist of Justice Lad” and an ending featuring the in-continuity return of a popular villain that you can’t miss! And what’s any of this have to do with the twisted Dr. Dibuk?!?
name: Fist of Cartoon

description:
The official adaptation of Transformers: Revenge of the Fallen picks up directly where the Destiny movie prequels leave off with this weekly series -- the Transformers' brutal war continues on Earth as the noble Autobots work with their human allies to end the threat of the treacherous Decepticons.

In the first part of the Official Transformers:Revenge of the Fallen movie adaptation, we see how the Fallen arrived to the earth million of years ago and that the Autobots are working with the goverment now.

Meanwhile Sam is moving to his college apartment where he mets with Alice and Leo Spitz.While he's still home, he drops a piece from the Allspark to the ground and things from the house transforms into mini robots. Bumblebee arrives and saves Sam and his parents but the house burns down.

Mikaela calls Sam and tells him that she break up with him because the distance between them.

Optimus arrives at Sam apartment and asks for Sam's help in order to restore peace to the universe but Sam ignores Optimus' help saying that this isn't his fight.

Same time, a group of decepticons arrive and resurrects Megatron.
name: Part 1

volume.name: Transformers: Revenge of the Fallen - Official Movie Adaptation

description: Dragon finishes up business beating up some gargoyles with TMNT and start to leave, but things aren't always what they seem. Now Savage Dragon and The Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles are of to find out why these gargoyles and other statues are suddenly coming to life. Will they be able to survive the answer they find?
name: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles / Savage Dragon Crossover

volume.name: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles-Savage Dragon Crossover

description:
Spirit seer and archmage-in-training Seance and his Rakshasa girlfriend Genn are on what's supposed to be a peaceful beach vacation in the mystic realm of Jade. Instead, they get caught up in bounty hunt for escaped criminals that gets them entangled with Grim Reaper-turned-waitress Dawn Brown and teenage-assassin-turned-waitress Suzume Satsujin, a dispute that will end up leading them to the underworld and back!

For the first time in seven years, Gold Digger and Ninja High School are crossing over in an epic mini-series, from the same talents that brought you Gold Digger: Tifanny and Charlotte! Don't miss it!

volume.name: Gold Digger/Ninja High School: Maidens Of Twilight

description: The final hour is at hand! Wizards, bounty hunters and grim reapers have all joined together to deal with the threat of accidental apocalypse, even if it means fighting a full-issue battle up a vertical mountain of lava! Love will be confessed, hearts will be broken, secrets revealed, and lust will rule... but in order to save the day, one of their own must be sacrificed!

volume.name: Gold Digger/Ninja High School: Maidens Of Twilight

description: Thanks to her student, the grass wizard Alena, Gina's excavation of T'uala has located a city-sized myconid pod in the molten rock surrounding the buried fortress, immune to the lava's heat. Within it, thousands of plant-like creatures resembling powerful, armored vehicles have been waiting for an opportunity to return to the world above. Gina's not about to let Alena examine the pod's plant-magic and botanical-tech secrets firsthand, as it's too dangerous. However, with a little help from fluffy-minded relic expert Aljabra, Alena might reach the myconid pod anyway... but will she live to regret meeting the evil of all roots?
name: The Chariot Champions

description: Batman Family Group Editor and longtime Batman writer Dennis O'Neil adapts the Tim Burton-Michael Keaton Batman Returns. Steve Erwin pencils with Jose Luis Garcia-Lopez inks and Tom McGraw colors under a Dave Dorman painted cover.
name: The Official Comic Adaptation of the Warner Bros. Motion Picture

description: The miniseries starring WildStorm's new "battlemage" continues! They're hip! They're happenin'! They're also dead! Johnny B. Dark & The Shades are blowin' into town, and all Hell is about to break loose! Fifty years ago, they sold their souls for the ultimate hotrod. Now, they want their lives back and they don't care whose souls they gotta' steal to get 'em! Can Jezebelle save Salem from these ghostly greasers before it's too late?
name: A Small Corner of Hell 2 of 6: "Shades and Shadows"

description: As the souls of her fellow high school students hang in the balance, Harper Harrison must face destiny and assume the mystical mantle of her ancestors by becoming the next Jezebelle! But first, she'll have to survive a reunion with her family's arch-nemesis: the demon Ghoulgotha!
name: A Small Corner of Hell 3 of 6: "An Angel in Disguise"

description: "Séance and Sensibility," Part 1. Harper Harrison is learning what it means to wear the Jezebelle mantle, but there are some things a fledging Battlemage simply should never attempt — such as contacting the dead, visiting the underworld, and opening a mystical rift between worlds! Things go horribly wrong as the techno-monster The Cretin and his legion of mecha-demons are unleashed upon the world!
name: A Small Corner of Hell 4 of 6: Seance & Sensibility

description: For centuries, Harper Harrison's family has fought the many faces of evil. But never before had her ancestors encountered a menace as bizarre as the extradimensional terror known as the Cretin! There's only one thing in the universe that can satisfy this mechanized monster's lust for conquest: magic. In order to achieve his twisted goals of revolution on his homeworld, he must have the power of the Soulstone. And the only way he's gonna get it is over Jezebelle's dead body!
name: A Small Corner of Hell 5 of 6: Someone to Watch Over Me

description: Not just Jezebelle's future, but the future of the entire Harrison heritage is on the line in the soul-shattering conclusion to WildStorm's mystical miniseries. Harper at last has learned what it means to be Jezebelle, and a hero. To right a terrible wrong, she travels to Hell, and finds it not a fire and brimstone inferno, but a dark mirror of her own high school. There, she fights not only for the soul of her condemned boyfriend Jake, but also for his redemption...and hers, as well.
name: A Small Corner of Hell 6 of 6

description:
Welcome to Gotham City, America's crime capital! There is a new force for the cause of justice - District Attorney Harvey Dent. And, a mysterious creature of the night, The Batman! Who is this Dark Knight? How is he connected to the dashing millionaire philanthropist Bruce Wayne? Everyone from the Gotham Police to Commissioner Gordon to reporter Alexander Knox and photographer Vicki Vale want to know.

This adaptation of the Tim Burton-directed Batman, brings Michael Keaton's Batman face-to-face, or mano y mano with Jack Nicholson's Joker! What scheme does the "Clown Prince of Crime" have up his sleeve to celebrate Gotham's bicentennial?
name: The Official Comic Adaptation of the Warner Bros. Motion Picture

description: Mickey 'the Nickel' Nicholson will do anything for a buck. A dirty prize- fighter, Mickey is hired by a mobster gone straight to infiltrate an underground boxing outfit in the small corrupt town of Overlook. His goal: to find the mobster's stolen 'rainy day' money and kill his wayward wife. In return, the mobster will assassinate a victim of Mickey's choice.
This issue was a Wizard Comics Magazine exclusive.
